acaa3ee1-09bc-40fc-b3b5-d2c139f830e5.title: Do you want to talk about lamps?

options.text: No, I'm more interested in impling jars.

effcf94c-7883-4f1e-90d0-b2d297d5e073.title: <player>
effcf94c-7883-4f1e-90d0-b2d297d5e073.text: Hi, I need fuel for a lamp.

7578cd99-24e1-4bf1-b679-38749670e570.title: <player>
7578cd99-24e1-4bf1-b679-38749670e570.text: I'd better go and get the repellent.

42d84433-72b3-49eb-81f7-ac462389ea9f.title: Chemist
42d84433-72b3-49eb-81f7-ac462389ea9f.text:
Hello there, the fuel you need is lamp oil, do you need
help making it?

16c96161-bfab-408a-84d9-cdaa24c22489.title: Chemist
16c96161-bfab-408a-84d9-cdaa24c22489.text: Well, it should be ideally suited to your task.

c7a3d9dd-8dc3-4338-9b70-6081d739dbe0.title: Chemist
c7a3d9dd-8dc3-4338-9b70-6081d739dbe0.text:
Good to hear, sorry but I have a few things to do right
now.

6153ec7b-ee19-4e78-b599-8f3af257a68c.title: Chemist
6153ec7b-ee19-4e78-b599-8f3af257a68c.text:
Just put ordinary swamp tar in, and then use a lantern
or lamp to get the oil out.

11d28291-9dcf-438e-a137-a40c06b92b66.title: Chemist
11d28291-9dcf-438e-a137-a40c06b92b66.text:
It's really quite simple. You use the small still in here.
It's all set up, so there's no fiddling around with dials...

d612c8eb-2255-4349-9835-6760b74035fb.title: <player>
d612c8eb-2255-4349-9835-6760b74035fb.text: Well I'd better let you get on then.

a85b6f5a-3713-4f64-9c6f-c0b4e1b2ff76.title: <player>
a85b6f5a-3713-4f64-9c6f-c0b4e1b2ff76.text: I have a slightly odd question.

f926b05d-57b8-4159-88d7-bd661a137b70.title: Chemist
f926b05d-57b8-4159-88d7-bd661a137b70.text: Jolly good, the odder the better. I like oddities.

ed82b2a6-55a2-4bb9-9ee1-960f8a5a85f1.title: <player>
ed82b2a6-55a2-4bb9-9ee1-960f8a5a85f1.text:
Do you know how I might distil a mix of anchovy oil
and flowers so that it forms a layer on the inside of a
butterfly jar?

d518f329-82bc-4d33-bc0e-8d9dadde548e.title: Chemist
d518f329-82bc-4d33-bc0e-8d9dadde548e.text:
That is an odd question. I commend you for it. Why
would you want to do that?

25d91e66-6e1d-4a53-a7f8-dd6153425a29.title: <player>
25d91e66-6e1d-4a53-a7f8-dd6153425a29.text:
Apparently, if I can make a jar like this it will be useful
for storing implings in.

1a4ce7f0-7a2c-4f6b-b97a-af67a021bf05.title: Chemist
1a4ce7f0-7a2c-4f6b-b97a-af67a021bf05.text:
So, do you have any of this fish-and-flower flavoured oil
and a butterfly jar then?

64373ebb-c351-4470-8392-3cc2facc9460.title: Chemist
64373ebb-c351-4470-8392-3cc2facc9460.text:
If you go and get them then I may be able to help
you. I'm better at coming up with answers if the
questions are in my hands.

db4f3f3e-b4dd-455a-8325-ba96ab4cc737.title: Is there anything else you want to ask?

options.text: So how do you make anchovy oil?
Do you have a sieve I can use?
I'd better go and get the repellent.

544fe505-aa93-4bb3-8f45-c88536cb9895.title: <player>
544fe505-aa93-4bb3-8f45-c88536cb9895.text: So, how do you make anchovy oil?

5b2cb136-2a61-488c-adf3-d20600c6686f.title: Chemist
5b2cb136-2a61-488c-adf3-d20600c6686f.text:
Anchovies are pretty oily fish. I'd have thought you
could just grind them up and sieve out the bits. You'd
probably want to remove any water first - Cooking
should do that pretty well.

a9824b96-8eac-4705-841e-1cbffb166093.title: <player>
a9824b96-8eac-4705-841e-1cbffb166093.text: Do you have a sieve I can use?

a0074b66-3a68-44df-b0f1-1c1a18ccc831.title: Chemist
a0074b66-3a68-44df-b0f1-1c1a18ccc831.text:
Errm, yes. But you already have one. Two sieves is a
bit excessive, don't you think?

911b57cf-c95e-4fd5-a130-c7916ec00802.title: Chemist
911b57cf-c95e-4fd5-a130-c7916ec00802.text:
Errm, yes. Here, have this one. It's only been used for
sieving dead rats out of sewer water.

50cdb566-792d-4f3c-8c49-5057bf4b6333.title: <player>
50cdb566-792d-4f3c-8c49-5057bf4b6333.text:
Err, why? Actually, on second thoughts I don't want to
know.
